{"title_page": "Ros\u00e9 (singer)", "text_new": "{{short description|South Korean singer}}\n{{Use dmy dates|date=July 2019}}\n{{Use Australian English|date= May 2019}}\n{{distinguish|Rose (French singer)}}\n{{Infobox person\n| name               = Ros\u00e9 our QUEEN\n| image            = (180624) BLACKPINK fansign event at the AK Plaza in Bundang 012.jpg\n| caption          = Ros\u00e9 at a fan event in [[Bundang]], June 2018\n| alt              = Ros\u00e9 sits at a table holding a microphone, looking sideways.\n| birth_name         = Roseanne Park\n| other_names        = Park Chae-young\n| birth_date         = {{birth date and age|1997|02|11|df=yes}}\n| birth_place        = [[Auckland]], New Zealand\n| home_town          = [[Melbourne]], Australia\n| module             = {{Infobox musical artist|embed=yes\n| genre              = {{hlist|[[K-pop]]|[[Electronic dance music|EDM]]|[[hip hop music|hip hop]]}}\n| occupation       = Singer<!-- Being a celebrity with endorsements doesn't make you a model. -->\n| instrument       = Vocals<!-- Yes, she can play instruments. This is just for what she does professionally, which is singing. -->\n| background       = solo_singer\n| years_active     = 2012, 2016\u2013present\n| origin           = South Korea<!-- origin of musical career -->\n| label            = {{hlist|[[YG Entertainment|YG]]|[[Interscope Records|Interscope]]<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.billboard.com/articles/columns/pop/8481273/blackpink-interscope-records-umg-global-deal-yg-entertainment|title=BLACKPINK Sign With Interscope Records & UMG in Global Partnership With YG Entertainment: Exclusive|work=[[Billboard (magazine)|Billboard]]|date=22 October 2018|access-date=23 November 2018|last=Herman|first=Tamar}}</ref>}}\n| associated_acts  = {{hlist|[[Blackpink]]|[[YG Family]]}}\n| website          = <!-- {{URL|example.com}} or {{Official URL}} -->\n}}\n| signature          =\n| module2            = {{Infobox Korean name|child=yes\n| hangul          = {{linktext|\ubc15|\ucc44|\uc601}}\n| hanja           = {{linktext|\u6a38|\u5f69|\u82f1|}}\n| rr              = Bak Chae-yeong\n| mr              = Pak Ch'aey\u014fng\n| hangulstage     = {{linktext|\ub85c|\uc81c}}\n| rrstage         = Roje\n| mrstage         = Roje\n}}\n}}\n\n'''Roseanne Park'''<!-- Per the sources below, her birthname is Roseanne Park. --> (born 11 February 1997), better known by her stage name '''Ros\u00e9''' ({{ko-hhrm|\ub85c\uc81c}}), is a New Zealand <!-- She was born in New Zealand and grew up in Australia. --> singer currently based in South Korea. Ros\u00e9 signed with South Korean label [[YG Entertainment]] following an audition in 2012, training there for four years. She eventually made her debut as a vocalist in the girl group [[Blackpink]] in August 2016. As a solo artist, she has featured in labelmate [[G-Dragon]]'s 2012 track \"Without You\", which peaked at number ten on the [[Gaon Music Chart]].\n\n== Life and career ==\n=== 1997\u20132015: Early life and career ===\nRoseanne Park ({{ko-hhrm|\ubc15\ucc44\uc601}}; ''Park Chae-young'') was born on 11 February 1997<ref name=\"blackpinkINSTA\">{{Cite web |url=https://www.instagram.com/p/BfBTuV0Alks/ |title=BL\u039b\u0186KPI\u0418K on Instagram: \"#BLACKPINK #\ube14\ub799\ud551\ud06c #ROS\u00c9 #\ub85c\uc81c #HAPPYBIRTHDAY #2018_02_11 #YG\" |website=Instagram |language=en |access-date=2019-07-08}}</ref><ref name=\"ygTWITTER\">{{Cite web |url=https://twitter.com/ygent_official/status/962340411355234304 |title=HAPPY BIRTHDAY ROS\u00c9#BLACKPINK #\ube14\ub799\ud551\ud06c#2018_02_11 #HBD #\ub85c\uc81cpic.twitter.com/AJEnRLeSyD |last=FAMILY |first=YG |date=2018-02-10 |website=@ygent_official |language=en |access-date=2019-07-08}}</ref> in [[Auckland]], New Zealand, to South Korean immigrant parents.<ref name=\"scmp18\">{{cite news|url=https://www.scmp.com/culture/music/article/2163713/rose-blackpink-new-zealand-born-k-pop-singer-unique-voice-and|title=Rose from Blackpink \u2013 New Zealand-born K-pop singer with the unique voice and difficult dance moves|last=Kim|first=Nemo|date=12 September 2018|accessdate=28 May 2019|work=[[South China Morning Post]]}}</ref> She has one older sister. In 2004, at the age of seven, Ros\u00e9 and her family moved to [[Melbourne]], Australia.<ref name=\"smh\">{{cite news|url=https://www.smh.com.au/entertainment/music/blackpinks-rose-how-a-joke-turned-into-kpop-stardom-for-an-australian-singer-20170629-gx15a2.html|title=BlackPink's Rose: How a joke turned into K-pop stardom for an Australian singer|work=[[The Sydney Morning Herald]]|last=Wilder|first=Gabriel|date=27 June 2017|accessdate=28 May 2019}}</ref> Ros\u00e9 attended [[Canterbury Girls' Secondary College]] in Melbourne.<ref name=\"scmp19\">{{cite news|url=https://www.scmp.com/magazines/style/people-events/article/2185455/4-things-know-about-k-pop-star-rose-blackpinks-high|title=4 things to know about K-pop star Rose, BLACKPINK's high-note singer|last=Li|first=Caspar|date=11 February 2019|accessdate=28 May 2019|work=[[South China Morning Post]]}}</ref> She began singing and learned to play guitar and piano as a child and performed in church choirs.<ref name=\"smh\" /><ref name=\"scmp19\" />\n\nIn 2012, 15-year-old Ros\u00e9 attended an audition in Australia for South Korean record label [[YG Entertainment]] at her father's suggestion<ref name=\"smh\" /> and was ranked first among 700 participants.<ref>{{cite news|url=http://time.com/5562946/blackpink-k-pop-everything-to-know|work=[[Time (magazine)|Time]]|title=Everything to Know About K-Pop Group BLACKPINK|last=Moon|first=Kat|date=4 April 2019|accessdate=31 May 2019}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|url=https://entertain.naver.com/read?oid=052&aid=0001163639|title=[Y\uae30\ud68d\u2461]\uba64\ubc84\ub97c \uc54c\uba74 '\uc9c4\uc9dc' \ube14\ub799\ud551\ud06c\uac00 \ubcf4\uc778\ub2e4|lang=ko|work=YTN|date=7 July 2018|accessdate=28 May 2019|last=Ji|first=Seung-hoon}}</ref> Within two months she had signed with the label and moved to [[Seoul]].<ref name=\"scmp19\" /> Ros\u00e9 initially thought her father's idea was a joke due to the distance and difficulty of becoming a singer overseas, stating:\n\n{{blockquote|In Australia, I didn't think that there was much of a chance for me to become a singer, especially to become a K-pop star... I was living so far from the country that it never really occurred to me as a possibility.<ref name=smh />}}\n\nThe same year, Ros\u00e9 was given an opportunity to feature on labelmate [[G-Dragon]]'s song \"Without You\" off his [[extended play|EP]] ''[[One of a Kind (EP)|One of a Kind]]'' (2012). Her name was not publicised at the time of release with her credit revealed following her announcement as a Blackpink member.<ref>{{cite news|url=https://entertain.naver.com/read?oid=465&aid=0000002387|title=\ube14\ub799\ud551\ud06c, \uc9c0\ub09c 6\ub144\uc758 \ub370\ubdd4\uc0ac|lang=ko|date=17 August 2016|accessdate=28 May 2019|work=Ize|last=Lim|first=Soo-yeon}}</ref> The song peaked at number ten on South Korea's [[Gaon Music Chart]] and at number 15 on the [[K-pop Hot 100|''Billboard Korea'' K-pop Hot 100]].<ref name=\"wygaon\">{{cite web|url=http://gaonchart.co.kr/main/section/chart/online.gaon?nationGbn=T&serviceGbn=ALL&targetTime=39&hitYear=2012&termGbn=week|title=2012\ub144 39\uc8fc\ucc28 Digital Chart|lang=ko|accessdate=28 May 2019|publisher=[[Gaon Music Chart]]}}</ref><ref name=\"wy100\">{{cite web |url=http://www.billboard.com/artist/276219/g-dragon/chart?f=1175|title=G-Dragon Korea K-Pop Hot 100 Chart History|accessdate=28 May 2019|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20170925073129/http://www.billboard.com/artist/276219/g-dragon/chart?f=1175|archive-date=25 September 2017|url-status=dead}}</ref>\n\n=== 2016\u2013present: Debut with Blackpink ===\n{{see also|Blackpink}}\nRos\u00e9 trained at YGE for four years before her announcement as a member of [[Blackpink]] in June 2016. She was the last member to be revealed.<ref>{{cite news|url=https://entertain.naver.com/read?oid=109&aid=0003343019|title=YG, \uc0c8 \uac78\uadf8\ub8f9 \ub124\ubc88\uc9f8 \uba64\ubc84 \ub85c\uc81c \uacf5\uac1c..\ud638\uc8fc \ucd9c\uc2e0 \uc2e4\ub825\ud30c..'\uac15\ub82c'|lang=ko|work=Osen|date=22 June 2016|accessdate=28 May 2019|last=Sung|first=Mi-kyung}}</ref> The group debuted on 8 August 2016 with the [[single album]] ''Square One'' and lead singles \"[[Whistle (Blackpink song)|Whistle]]\" and [[Boombayah|<nowiki>''</nowiki>Boombayah]]\".<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.billboard.com/articles/columns/k-town/7476115/blackpink-debut-boombaya-whistle-world-digital-songs-chart|title=Blackpink's Major Debut: New K-Pop Girl Group Lands No. 1 & 2 on World Digital Songs Chart|last=Benjamin|first=Jeff|work=[[Billboard (magazine)|Billboard]]|date=16 August 2016|accessdate=30 May 2019}}</ref> \n\nThe singer has also appeared on a variety of broadcast programmes such as music shows ''[[King of Masked Singer]]'' and ''[[Fantastic Duo|Fantastic Duo 2]]''. Her vocal performance on ''King of Masked Singer'' was met with a warm reception by the audience, to which Ros\u00e9 commented that she \"didn't know if the audience would like [her] singing\" and that she felt \"happy and relieved\" at the positive result.<ref name=\"scmp18\" /> Ros\u00e9 later appeared as a performer on the second season of ''Fantastic Duo''. The show's production staff stated that her appearance was intended to \"reveal Ros\u00e9's vocal appeal, which is different from Blackpink\".<ref name=\"fd2\">{{cite news|url=https://entertain.naver.com/ranking/read?oid=109&aid=0003591247|title=[Oh!\uc388 \ucef7]'\ud310\ub4c02' \ub85c\uc81c \"YG\uc624\ub514\uc158, 400:1 \uacbd\uc7c1 \ub6ab\uace0 \ud569\uaca9\"|lang=ko|date=4 August 2017|accessdate=29 May 2019|last=Park|first=Chan-soo|work=Osen}}</ref>\n\n== Artistry ==\nRos\u00e9's voice has received acknowledgement in the K-pop industry for its distinct vocal [[timbre]], following her debut as a member of Blackpink.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://entertain.naver.com/now/read?oid=109&aid=0003666569|title=[\ud654\ubcf4] \ube14\ub799\ud551\ud06c \ub85c\uc81c \"\ubaa9\uc18c\ub9ac \ud2b9\uc774\ud55c \uc904 \ubab0\ub790\ub2e4..\uc120\ubb3c \ubc1b\uc740 \uae30\ubd84\"|work=Osen|date=22 November 2017|accessdate=29 May 2019|last=Lee|first=So-dam|lang=ko}}</ref> Filipina critic Almira Blancada, writing for [[ABS-CBN]], stated that \"it's hard to find an idol [singer] who stands out from the rest\" due to their \"common singing style\", but \"you would know it's Ros\u00e9 singing in a heartbeat\".<ref name=\"rcbn\">{{cite news|url=https://lifestyle.abs-cbn.com/articles/7226/chalk/in-focus-times-blackpinks-ros-showed-off-her-vocal-prowess/|title=In Focus: Times BLACKPINK's Ros\u00e9 Showed Off Her Vocal Prowess|last=Blancada|first=Almira|date=22 December 2018|accessdate=30 May 2019|publisher=[[ABS-CBN]]}}</ref> Following Ros\u00e9's performance on an episode of ''Fantastic Duo 2'', South Korean singer [[Gummy (singer)|Gummy]], who Ros\u00e9 cited as a musical role model,<ref name=\"fd2\" /> stated that \"[Ros\u00e9's] voice is so unique, it's the [type of] voice young people love\".<ref>{{cite AV media|date=6 August 2017|title= \ube14\ub799\ud551\ud06c \ub85c\uc81c, \uac70\ubbf8 \uc120\ubc30 \uc55e \ub5a8\ub9ac\ub294 \uc5f4\ucc3d \u2018Irreplaceable\u2019 \u300aFantastic Duo 2\u300b \ud310\ud0c0\uc2a4\ud2f1 \ub4c0\uc624 2 EP19|medium= Television show|language=ko|access-date=30 May 2019|format=video|time=2:30|location= YouTube|publisher=[[Seoul Broadcasting System|SBS]]|url=https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=BZY3F6ZSMhc}}</ref> As a musician, Ros\u00e9 considers American singer [[Tori Kelly]] an inspiration on her musical style.<ref>{{cite magazine|title=Interview with Ros\u00e9 of Blackpink: Ceci Magazine|lang=ko|magazine=Ceci Magazine|location=Seoul}}</ref>\n\n== Other ventures ==\n=== Endorsements ===\nIn 2018, Ros\u00e9 and fellow Blackpink member [[Jisoo (singer, born 1995)|Jisoo]] were selected as endorsement models for the South Korean cosmetics brand Kiss Me.<ref>{{cite news|url=https://entertain.naver.com/read?oid=112&aid=0003078077|title=\ube14\ub799\ud551\ud06c \uc9c0\uc218X\ub85c\uc81c, \uba54\uc774\ud06c\uc5c5 \ube0c\ub79c\ub4dc \ubaa8\ub378 \ubc1c\ud0c1..\ud2b8\ub80c\ub514 \ub9e4\ub825UP|lang=ko|work=[[The Korea Herald]]|date=27 September 2018|accessdate=29 May 2019|last=Kim|first=Na-yoo}}</ref> In October 2019, Ros\u00e9 was revealed as a promotional model for the [[Perfect World Entertainment]]'s [[Massively multiplayer online role-playing game|MMORPG]] ''Perfect World Mobile''.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.oneesports.gg/mobile-games/blackpinks-rose-revealed-as-the-face-of-mmorpg-perfect-world/|title=Blackpink's Ros\u00e9 revealed as the face of MMORPG Perfect World|date=2019-10-20|website=ONE Esports|language=en-US|access-date=2019-10-21}}</ref> In November 2019, revealed that Ros\u00e9 is the new Brand Ambassador of Yves Saint Laurent by Anthony Vaccarello.<ref>https://www.forbes.com/sites/nadjasayej/2020/02/21/how-the-k-pop-craze-is-taking-over-fashion-week/#67f95dfb75c5}}</ref>\n\n=== Influence ===\nIn April 2019, Ros\u00e9 was the ninth most-followed K-pop idol on [[Instagram]] with over 13 million followers.<!-- Do not update this number without providing a new source --><ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.eonline.com/ap/news/1032645/blackpink-s-lisa-is-now-officially-the-most-followed-k-pop-idol-on-instagram|title=BLACKPINK's Lisa is Now Officially the Most Followed K-Pop Idol on Instagram|work=[[E! News]]|last=Tan|first=Pakkee|date=15 April 2019|accessdate=30 May 2019}}</ref> Ros\u00e9 has appeared on the Korean Business Research Institute's female celebrity brand reputation list since 2018,<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.rekorea.net/bbs/board.php?bo_table=repu4&wr_id=279&page=1|title=[\ube0c\ub79c\ub4dc\ud3c9\ud310] \uac78\uadf8\ub8f9 \uac1c\uc778 \ube0c\ub79c\ub4dc 2018\ub144 8\uc6d4 \ube45\ub370\uc774\ud130 \ubd84\uc11d\uacb0\uacfc...1\uc704 \ub808\ub4dc\ubca8\ubcb3 \uc2ac\uae30, 2\uc704 \ube14\ub799\ud551\ud06c \uc81c\ub2c8, 3\uc704 \ub9c8\ub9c8\ubb34\u2026|lang=ko|date=19 August 2018|accessdate=30 May 2019|publisher=Korean Business Research Institute}}</ref> a chart that tracks the Korean celebrities with the most online searches and engagements. She has also reached the top 20.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.rekorea.net/bbs/board.php?bo_table=repu4&wr_id=342&page=1|title=[\ube0c\ub79c\ub4dc\ud3c9\ud310] \uac78\uadf8\ub8f9 \uac1c\uc778 \ube0c\ub79c\ub4dc 2019\ub144 2\uc6d4 \ube45\ub370\uc774\ud130 \ubd84\uc11d\uacb0\uacfc...1\uc704 \ube14\ub799\ud551\ud06c \uc81c\ub2c8, 2\uc704 \uc5ec\uc790\uce5c\uad6c \uc18c\uc6d0, 3\uc704 \ud2b8\uc640\uc774\u2026|lang=ko|date=17 February 2019|accessdate=30 May 2019|publisher=Korean Business Research Institute}}</ref>\n\n== Discography ==\n[[File:20190106 (NEWSEN) \ube14\ub799\ud551\ud06c(BLACKPINK), \uc218\uc90d\uc740 \ub9ce\uc740 \uc18c\ub140\uc9c0\ub9cc \ub3cb\ubcf4\uc774\ub294 \uc544\ub984\ub2e4\uc6b4 \ubbf8\ubaa8 (Golden Disc Awards 2019) (3).jpg|Ros\u00e9 at the [[33rd Golden Disc Awards]], January 2019.|thumb|upright|alt=Ros\u00e9 seen from the shoulders up, looks forward, slightly away from the camera.]]\n{{for|Ros\u00e9's discography as a member of Blackpink|Blackpink discography}}\n\n=== As featured artist ===\n{| class=\"wikitable plainrowheaders\" style=\"text-align:center;\" border=\"1\"\n! rowspan=\"3\" style=\"width:18em;\" | Title\n! rowspan=\"3\" style=\"width:2em;\"| Year\n! colspan=\"2\" |Peak chart positions\n! rowspan=\"3\" style=\"width:10em;\"| Sales\n! rowspan=\"3\" style=\"width:8em;\" | Album\n|-\n! scope=\"col\" colspan=\"2\" | KOR\n|-\n! scope=\"col\" scope=\"col\" style=\"width:2.5em;font-size:90%;\"|[[Gaon Chart|<small>Gaon</small>]]<br /><ref name=\"wygaon\" />\n! scope=\"col\" scope=\"col\" style=\"width:2.5em;font-size:90%;\"|[[Korea K-Pop Hot 100|<small>Hot</small>]]<br /><ref name=\"wy100\"/>\n|-\n! scope=\"row\" | \"Without You\" {{small|(\uacb0\uad6d; ''Gyeolguk'')<!-- Keep romanization per Wikipedia policies on non-English text. -->}}<br />{{small|([[G-Dragon]] {{abbreviation|feat.|featuring}} Ros\u00e9)}}{{efn|Credited as \"? of YG New Girl Group\" at the time of the release.<ref name=\"wy dl year\"/>}}\n| 2012\n| 10 || 15\n|\n* KOR: 646,074<ref name=\"wy dl year\">{{cite web|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20160819003852/http://gaonchart.co.kr/main/section/chart/online.gaon?pageNo=3&serviceGbn=S1020&termGbn=year&hitYear=2012&targetTime=12&nationGbn=K|url=http://gaonchart.co.kr/main/section/chart/online.gaon?nationGbn=T&pageNo=3&serviceGbn=S1020&targetTime=2012&hitYear=2012&termGbn=year|title=Gaon Download Chart of 2012|archivedate=19 August 2016|accessdate=29 May 2019}}</ref>\n|''[[One of a Kind (EP)|One of a Kind]]''\n|-\n|}\n{{notelist}}\n\n== Filmography ==\n{{for|her appearances as a member of Blackpink|Blackpink#Filmography}}\n{{see also|Blackpink videography}}\n=== Television ===\n{| class=\"wikitable\"\n|+\n!Year\n!Title\n!Network\n!Role\n!Notes\n!{{abbreviation|Ref.|References}}\n|-\n|rowspan=2|2017\n| ''[[King of Mask Singer]]''\n| [[Munhwa Broadcasting Corporation|MBC]]\n| Contestant \"Circus Girl\"\n| Episodes 103\u2013104\n|<ref>{{cite news|url=https://entertain.naver.com/read?oid=404&aid=0000171450|title='\ubcf5\uba74\uac00\uc655' \ube14\ub799\ud551\ud06c \ub85c\uc81c, \uc5c4\ub9c8 \uc5b8\uae09\uc5d0 \ub208\ubb3c \uc648\uce75 \"\uc790\ub791\uc2a4\ub7ec\uc6b4 \ub538 \ub418\uaca0\ub2e4\"|lang=ko|work=ENews24|date=26 March 2017|accessdate=29 May 2019|last=Jo|first=Hae-jin}}</ref>\n|-\n|''[[Fantastic Duo]]''\n|[[Seoul Broadcasting System|SBS]]\n|Contestant \"Australia 400:1\"\n|Season 2, Episodes 19\u201320\n|<ref name=fd2/>\n|-\n|}\n\n==See also==\n* [[List of awards and nominations received by Blackpink]]\n\n== References ==\n{{reflist}}\n\n== External links ==\n* {{commons cat inline|Ros\u00e9 Park|Ros\u00e9}}\n\n{{Blackpink}}\n{{Authority control}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Rose}}\n[[Category:1997 births]]\n[[Category:Living people]]\n[[Category:Musicians from Melbourne]]\n[[Category:Blackpink members]]\n[[Category:New Zealand female singers]]\n[[Category:Korean-language singers]]\n[[Category:New Zealand people of South Korean descent]]\n[[Category:K-pop singers]]\n[[Category:21st-century women singers]]\n[[Category:21st-century New Zealand singers]]\n[[Category:New Zealand expatriates in Australia]]\n[[Category:New Zealand expatriates in South Korea]]\n[[Category:Musicians from Auckland]]\n[[Category:King of Mask Singer contestants]]\n", "text_old": "{{short description|South Korean singer}}\n{{Use dmy dates|date=July 2019}}\n{{Use Australian English|date= May 2019}}\n{{distinguish|Rose (French singer)}}\n{{Infobox person\n| name               = Ros\u00e9\n| image            = (180624) BLACKPINK fansign event at the AK Plaza in Bundang 012.jpg\n| caption          = Ros\u00e9 at a fan event in [[Bundang]], June 2018\n| alt              = Ros\u00e9 sits at a table holding a microphone, looking sideways.\n| birth_name         = Roseanne Park\n| other_names        = Park Chae-young\n| birth_date         = {{birth date and age|1997|02|11|df=yes}}\n| birth_place        = [[Auckland]], New Zealand\n| home_town          = [[Melbourne]], Australia\n| module             = {{Infobox musical artist|embed=yes\n| genre              = {{hlist|[[K-pop]]|[[Electronic dance music|EDM]]|[[hip hop music|hip hop]]}}\n| occupation       = Singer<!-- Being a celebrity with endorsements doesn't make you a model. -->\n| instrument       = Vocals<!-- Yes, she can play instruments. This is just for what she does professionally, which is singing. -->\n| background       = solo_singer\n| years_active     = 2012, 2016\u2013present\n| origin           = South Korea<!-- origin of musical career -->\n| label            = {{hlist|[[YG Entertainment|YG]]|[[Interscope Records|Interscope]]<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.billboard.com/articles/columns/pop/8481273/blackpink-interscope-records-umg-global-deal-yg-entertainment|title=BLACKPINK Sign With Interscope Records & UMG in Global Partnership With YG Entertainment: Exclusive|work=[[Billboard (magazine)|Billboard]]|date=22 October 2018|access-date=23 November 2018|last=Herman|first=Tamar}}</ref>}}\n| associated_acts  = {{hlist|[[Blackpink]]|[[YG Family]]}}\n| website          = <!-- {{URL|example.com}} or {{Official URL}} -->\n}}\n| signature          =\n| module2            = {{Infobox Korean name|child=yes\n| hangul          = {{linktext|\ubc15|\ucc44|\uc601}}\n| hanja           = {{linktext|\u6a38|\u5f69|\u82f1|}}\n| rr              = Bak Chae-yeong\n| mr              = Pak Ch'aey\u014fng\n| hangulstage     = {{linktext|\ub85c|\uc81c}}\n| rrstage         = Roje\n| mrstage         = Roje\n}}\n}}\n\n'''Roseanne Park'''<!-- Per the sources below, her birthname is Roseanne Park. --> (born 11 February 1997), better known by her stage name '''Ros\u00e9''' ({{ko-hhrm|\ub85c\uc81c}}), is a New Zealand <!-- She was born in New Zealand and grew up in Australia. --> singer currently based in South Korea. Ros\u00e9 signed with South Korean label [[YG Entertainment]] following an audition in 2012, training there for four years. She eventually made her debut as a vocalist in the girl group [[Blackpink]] in August 2016. As a solo artist, she has featured in labelmate [[G-Dragon]]'s 2012 track \"Without You\", which peaked at number ten on the [[Gaon Music Chart]].\n\n== Life and career ==\n=== 1997\u20132015: Early life and career ===\nRoseanne Park ({{ko-hhrm|\ubc15\ucc44\uc601}}; ''Park Chae-young'') was born on 11 February 1997<ref name=\"blackpinkINSTA\">{{Cite web |url=https://www.instagram.com/p/BfBTuV0Alks/ |title=BL\u039b\u0186KPI\u0418K on Instagram: \"#BLACKPINK #\ube14\ub799\ud551\ud06c #ROS\u00c9 #\ub85c\uc81c #HAPPYBIRTHDAY #2018_02_11 #YG\" |website=Instagram |language=en |access-date=2019-07-08}}</ref><ref name=\"ygTWITTER\">{{Cite web |url=https://twitter.com/ygent_official/status/962340411355234304 |title=HAPPY BIRTHDAY ROS\u00c9#BLACKPINK #\ube14\ub799\ud551\ud06c#2018_02_11 #HBD #\ub85c\uc81cpic.twitter.com/AJEnRLeSyD |last=FAMILY |first=YG |date=2018-02-10 |website=@ygent_official |language=en |access-date=2019-07-08}}</ref> in [[Auckland]], New Zealand, to South Korean immigrant parents.<ref name=\"scmp18\">{{cite news|url=https://www.scmp.com/culture/music/article/2163713/rose-blackpink-new-zealand-born-k-pop-singer-unique-voice-and|title=Rose from Blackpink \u2013 New Zealand-born K-pop singer with the unique voice and difficult dance moves|last=Kim|first=Nemo|date=12 September 2018|accessdate=28 May 2019|work=[[South China Morning Post]]}}</ref> She has one older sister. In 2004, at the age of seven, Ros\u00e9 and her family moved to [[Melbourne]], Australia.<ref name=\"smh\">{{cite news|url=https://www.smh.com.au/entertainment/music/blackpinks-rose-how-a-joke-turned-into-kpop-stardom-for-an-australian-singer-20170629-gx15a2.html|title=BlackPink's Rose: How a joke turned into K-pop stardom for an Australian singer|work=[[The Sydney Morning Herald]]|last=Wilder|first=Gabriel|date=27 June 2017|accessdate=28 May 2019}}</ref> Ros\u00e9 attended [[Canterbury Girls' Secondary College]] in Melbourne.<ref name=\"scmp19\">{{cite news|url=https://www.scmp.com/magazines/style/people-events/article/2185455/4-things-know-about-k-pop-star-rose-blackpinks-high|title=4 things to know about K-pop star Rose, BLACKPINK's high-note singer|last=Li|first=Caspar|date=11 February 2019|accessdate=28 May 2019|work=[[South China Morning Post]]}}</ref> She began singing and learned to play guitar and piano as a child and performed in church choirs.<ref name=\"smh\" /><ref name=\"scmp19\" />\n\nIn 2012, 15-year-old Ros\u00e9 attended an audition in Australia for South Korean record label [[YG Entertainment]] at her father's suggestion<ref name=\"smh\" /> and was ranked first among 700 participants.<ref>{{cite news|url=http://time.com/5562946/blackpink-k-pop-everything-to-know|work=[[Time (magazine)|Time]]|title=Everything to Know About K-Pop Group BLACKPINK|last=Moon|first=Kat|date=4 April 2019|accessdate=31 May 2019}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|url=https://entertain.naver.com/read?oid=052&aid=0001163639|title=[Y\uae30\ud68d\u2461]\uba64\ubc84\ub97c \uc54c\uba74 '\uc9c4\uc9dc' \ube14\ub799\ud551\ud06c\uac00 \ubcf4\uc778\ub2e4|lang=ko|work=YTN|date=7 July 2018|accessdate=28 May 2019|last=Ji|first=Seung-hoon}}</ref> Within two months she had signed with the label and moved to [[Seoul]].<ref name=\"scmp19\" /> Ros\u00e9 initially thought her father's idea was a joke due to the distance and difficulty of becoming a singer overseas, stating:\n\n{{blockquote|In Australia, I didn't think that there was much of a chance for me to become a singer, especially to become a K-pop star... I was living so far from the country that it never really occurred to me as a possibility.<ref name=smh />}}\n\nThe same year, Ros\u00e9 was given an opportunity to feature on labelmate [[G-Dragon]]'s song \"Without You\" off his [[extended play|EP]] ''[[One of a Kind (EP)|One of a Kind]]'' (2012). Her name was not publicised at the time of release with her credit revealed following her announcement as a Blackpink member.<ref>{{cite news|url=https://entertain.naver.com/read?oid=465&aid=0000002387|title=\ube14\ub799\ud551\ud06c, \uc9c0\ub09c 6\ub144\uc758 \ub370\ubdd4\uc0ac|lang=ko|date=17 August 2016|accessdate=28 May 2019|work=Ize|last=Lim|first=Soo-yeon}}</ref> The song peaked at number ten on South Korea's [[Gaon Music Chart]] and at number 15 on the [[K-pop Hot 100|''Billboard Korea'' K-pop Hot 100]].<ref name=\"wygaon\">{{cite web|url=http://gaonchart.co.kr/main/section/chart/online.gaon?nationGbn=T&serviceGbn=ALL&targetTime=39&hitYear=2012&termGbn=week|title=2012\ub144 39\uc8fc\ucc28 Digital Chart|lang=ko|accessdate=28 May 2019|publisher=[[Gaon Music Chart]]}}</ref><ref name=\"wy100\">{{cite web |url=http://www.billboard.com/artist/276219/g-dragon/chart?f=1175|title=G-Dragon Korea K-Pop Hot 100 Chart History|accessdate=28 May 2019|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20170925073129/http://www.billboard.com/artist/276219/g-dragon/chart?f=1175|archive-date=25 September 2017|url-status=dead}}</ref>\n\n=== 2016\u2013present: Debut with Blackpink ===\n{{see also|Blackpink}}\nRos\u00e9 trained at YGE for four years before her announcement as a member of [[Blackpink]] in June 2016. She was the last member to be revealed.<ref>{{cite news|url=https://entertain.naver.com/read?oid=109&aid=0003343019|title=YG, \uc0c8 \uac78\uadf8\ub8f9 \ub124\ubc88\uc9f8 \uba64\ubc84 \ub85c\uc81c \uacf5\uac1c..\ud638\uc8fc \ucd9c\uc2e0 \uc2e4\ub825\ud30c..'\uac15\ub82c'|lang=ko|work=Osen|date=22 June 2016|accessdate=28 May 2019|last=Sung|first=Mi-kyung}}</ref> The group debuted on 8 August 2016 with the [[single album]] ''Square One'' and lead singles \"[[Whistle (Blackpink song)|Whistle]]\" and [[Boombayah|<nowiki>''</nowiki>Boombayah]]\".<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.billboard.com/articles/columns/k-town/7476115/blackpink-debut-boombaya-whistle-world-digital-songs-chart|title=Blackpink's Major Debut: New K-Pop Girl Group Lands No. 1 & 2 on World Digital Songs Chart|last=Benjamin|first=Jeff|work=[[Billboard (magazine)|Billboard]]|date=16 August 2016|accessdate=30 May 2019}}</ref> \n\nThe singer has also appeared on a variety of broadcast programmes such as music shows ''[[King of Masked Singer]]'' and ''[[Fantastic Duo|Fantastic Duo 2]]''. Her vocal performance on ''King of Masked Singer'' was met with a warm reception by the audience, to which Ros\u00e9 commented that she \"didn't know if the audience would like [her] singing\" and that she felt \"happy and relieved\" at the positive result.<ref name=\"scmp18\" /> Ros\u00e9 later appeared as a performer on the second season of ''Fantastic Duo''. The show's production staff stated that her appearance was intended to \"reveal Ros\u00e9's vocal appeal, which is different from Blackpink\".<ref name=\"fd2\">{{cite news|url=https://entertain.naver.com/ranking/read?oid=109&aid=0003591247|title=[Oh!\uc388 \ucef7]'\ud310\ub4c02' \ub85c\uc81c \"YG\uc624\ub514\uc158, 400:1 \uacbd\uc7c1 \ub6ab\uace0 \ud569\uaca9\"|lang=ko|date=4 August 2017|accessdate=29 May 2019|last=Park|first=Chan-soo|work=Osen}}</ref>\n\n== Artistry ==\nRos\u00e9's voice has received acknowledgement in the K-pop industry for its distinct vocal [[timbre]], following her debut as a member of Blackpink.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://entertain.naver.com/now/read?oid=109&aid=0003666569|title=[\ud654\ubcf4] \ube14\ub799\ud551\ud06c \ub85c\uc81c \"\ubaa9\uc18c\ub9ac \ud2b9\uc774\ud55c \uc904 \ubab0\ub790\ub2e4..\uc120\ubb3c \ubc1b\uc740 \uae30\ubd84\"|work=Osen|date=22 November 2017|accessdate=29 May 2019|last=Lee|first=So-dam|lang=ko}}</ref> Filipina critic Almira Blancada, writing for [[ABS-CBN]], stated that \"it's hard to find an idol [singer] who stands out from the rest\" due to their \"common singing style\", but \"you would know it's Ros\u00e9 singing in a heartbeat\".<ref name=\"rcbn\">{{cite news|url=https://lifestyle.abs-cbn.com/articles/7226/chalk/in-focus-times-blackpinks-ros-showed-off-her-vocal-prowess/|title=In Focus: Times BLACKPINK's Ros\u00e9 Showed Off Her Vocal Prowess|last=Blancada|first=Almira|date=22 December 2018|accessdate=30 May 2019|publisher=[[ABS-CBN]]}}</ref> Following Ros\u00e9's performance on an episode of ''Fantastic Duo 2'', South Korean singer [[Gummy (singer)|Gummy]], who Ros\u00e9 cited as a musical role model,<ref name=\"fd2\" /> stated that \"[Ros\u00e9's] voice is so unique, it's the [type of] voice young people love\".<ref>{{cite AV media|date=6 August 2017|title= \ube14\ub799\ud551\ud06c \ub85c\uc81c, \uac70\ubbf8 \uc120\ubc30 \uc55e \ub5a8\ub9ac\ub294 \uc5f4\ucc3d \u2018Irreplaceable\u2019 \u300aFantastic Duo 2\u300b \ud310\ud0c0\uc2a4\ud2f1 \ub4c0\uc624 2 EP19|medium= Television show|language=ko|access-date=30 May 2019|format=video|time=2:30|location= YouTube|publisher=[[Seoul Broadcasting System|SBS]]|url=https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=BZY3F6ZSMhc}}</ref> As a musician, Ros\u00e9 considers American singer [[Tori Kelly]] an inspiration on her musical style.<ref>{{cite magazine|title=Interview with Ros\u00e9 of Blackpink: Ceci Magazine|lang=ko|magazine=Ceci Magazine|location=Seoul}}</ref>\n\n== Other ventures ==\n=== Endorsements ===\nIn 2018, Ros\u00e9 and fellow Blackpink member [[Jisoo (singer, born 1995)|Jisoo]] were selected as endorsement models for the South Korean cosmetics brand Kiss Me.<ref>{{cite news|url=https://entertain.naver.com/read?oid=112&aid=0003078077|title=\ube14\ub799\ud551\ud06c \uc9c0\uc218X\ub85c\uc81c, \uba54\uc774\ud06c\uc5c5 \ube0c\ub79c\ub4dc \ubaa8\ub378 \ubc1c\ud0c1..\ud2b8\ub80c\ub514 \ub9e4\ub825UP|lang=ko|work=[[The Korea Herald]]|date=27 September 2018|accessdate=29 May 2019|last=Kim|first=Na-yoo}}</ref> In October 2019, Ros\u00e9 was revealed as a promotional model for the [[Perfect World Entertainment]]'s [[Massively multiplayer online role-playing game|MMORPG]] ''Perfect World Mobile''.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.oneesports.gg/mobile-games/blackpinks-rose-revealed-as-the-face-of-mmorpg-perfect-world/|title=Blackpink's Ros\u00e9 revealed as the face of MMORPG Perfect World|date=2019-10-20|website=ONE Esports|language=en-US|access-date=2019-10-21}}</ref> In November 2019, revealed that Ros\u00e9 is the new Brand Ambassador of Yves Saint Laurent by Anthony Vaccarello.<ref>https://www.forbes.com/sites/nadjasayej/2020/02/21/how-the-k-pop-craze-is-taking-over-fashion-week/#67f95dfb75c5}}</ref>\n\n=== Influence ===\nIn April 2019, Ros\u00e9 was the ninth most-followed K-pop idol on [[Instagram]] with over 13 million followers.<!-- Do not update this number without providing a new source --><ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.eonline.com/ap/news/1032645/blackpink-s-lisa-is-now-officially-the-most-followed-k-pop-idol-on-instagram|title=BLACKPINK's Lisa is Now Officially the Most Followed K-Pop Idol on Instagram|work=[[E! News]]|last=Tan|first=Pakkee|date=15 April 2019|accessdate=30 May 2019}}</ref> Ros\u00e9 has appeared on the Korean Business Research Institute's female celebrity brand reputation list since 2018,<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.rekorea.net/bbs/board.php?bo_table=repu4&wr_id=279&page=1|title=[\ube0c\ub79c\ub4dc\ud3c9\ud310] \uac78\uadf8\ub8f9 \uac1c\uc778 \ube0c\ub79c\ub4dc 2018\ub144 8\uc6d4 \ube45\ub370\uc774\ud130 \ubd84\uc11d\uacb0\uacfc...1\uc704 \ub808\ub4dc\ubca8\ubcb3 \uc2ac\uae30, 2\uc704 \ube14\ub799\ud551\ud06c \uc81c\ub2c8, 3\uc704 \ub9c8\ub9c8\ubb34\u2026|lang=ko|date=19 August 2018|accessdate=30 May 2019|publisher=Korean Business Research Institute}}</ref> a chart that tracks the Korean celebrities with the most online searches and engagements. She has also reached the top 20.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.rekorea.net/bbs/board.php?bo_table=repu4&wr_id=342&page=1|title=[\ube0c\ub79c\ub4dc\ud3c9\ud310] \uac78\uadf8\ub8f9 \uac1c\uc778 \ube0c\ub79c\ub4dc 2019\ub144 2\uc6d4 \ube45\ub370\uc774\ud130 \ubd84\uc11d\uacb0\uacfc...1\uc704 \ube14\ub799\ud551\ud06c \uc81c\ub2c8, 2\uc704 \uc5ec\uc790\uce5c\uad6c \uc18c\uc6d0, 3\uc704 \ud2b8\uc640\uc774\u2026|lang=ko|date=17 February 2019|accessdate=30 May 2019|publisher=Korean Business Research Institute}}</ref>\n\n== Discography ==\n[[File:20190106 (NEWSEN) \ube14\ub799\ud551\ud06c(BLACKPINK), \uc218\uc90d\uc740 \ub9ce\uc740 \uc18c\ub140\uc9c0\ub9cc \ub3cb\ubcf4\uc774\ub294 \uc544\ub984\ub2e4\uc6b4 \ubbf8\ubaa8 (Golden Disc Awards 2019) (3).jpg|Ros\u00e9 at the [[33rd Golden Disc Awards]], January 2019.|thumb|upright|alt=Ros\u00e9 seen from the shoulders up, looks forward, slightly away from the camera.]]\n{{for|Ros\u00e9's discography as a member of Blackpink|Blackpink discography}}\n\n=== As featured artist ===\n{| class=\"wikitable plainrowheaders\" style=\"text-align:center;\" border=\"1\"\n! rowspan=\"3\" style=\"width:18em;\" | Title\n! rowspan=\"3\" style=\"width:2em;\"| Year\n! colspan=\"2\" |